In an exclusive interview with CNBC's Hadley Gamble,  Lebanese Prime Minister Saad Hariri discussed the country's challenging economic situation, its place in the Middle East, the influence of Hezbollah and his commitment to stamp out corruption, amongst other issues.

To read more from the interview, head to cnbc.com/lebanon/

